notesStmt.note: Folio 1r contains an Arabic-Hebrew record relating to a transaction concerning this manuscript, signed by three witnesses, Zekharya ben Se'adya, Zekharya ben Shelomoh and Shelomoh ben Se'adya.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 26; written lines: 26; Uniform layout, with visible ruling with a hard-point. Catchwords on every verso.
